name: CmR
description: Versus ad repetendum for the communion

name: Cn
description: Cantio, Cantiones (paraliturgical sacred songs with poetic and often strophic Latin or vernacular texts)

name: CnV
description: Cantio Verse (strophe of paraliturgical sacred poetic text)

name: D
description: Dramatic element (used for items of liturgical drama that are not otherwise rubricked)

name: [G]
description: Mass chant (a generic code used in the earliest Cantus indices)

name: [GV]
description: Verse for a Mass chant (a generic code used in the earliest Cantus indices)

name: InR
description: Versus ad repetendum for the introit

name: IP
description: Invitatory psalm (when fully written out and notated)

name: L
description: Lesson (when fully written out and notated)

name: Li
description: Litany (and litany verses if listed together in the same record)

name: [M]
description: "Miscellaneous" (a descriptor used in the earliest versions of Cantus for the Te Deum, Versus in Triduo, prosulae - to be replaced by Va=Varia)

name: [MO]
description: Mass Ordinary  (a generic code used in the earliest Cantus indices)

name: Or
description: Oratio / Prayer (when written out and notated)

name: Pn
description: Pater noster (when written out and notated)

name: Tp
description: Trope (broadly); see also specific types of tropes, such as Psl (prosula) and TpBD (troped Benedicamus domino)

name: VRS
description: Versus (Hispanic rite, applied to a number of quite different types of pieces in the sources, including single verses of Scripture not attached to any parent chant as well as more lengthy poetic texts; seebRandel, Index, xvii)
